<table width="600">
	<tr>
		<td>
			<h1 align="center">QBIC</h1>
			<hr>			
		
			<p><b>Developed by:</b><br> IBM Almaden Research Center, CA</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Features:</b><br> 
			<u>Color:</u> Uses 3D average color vector of an object or the whole image.<br>
			<u>Texture:</u> Uses coarseness, contrast, and directionality.<br>
			<u>Shape:</u> Uses area, circularity, eccentricity, major axis orientation and a set of algebraic moment invariants.
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Matching:</b><br>
			Weighted Euclidean distance for color, texture, and shape.
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Indexing:</b><br>
			Uses R*-tree data structure for indexing.
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Querying:</b><br>
			Query based on example, user-constructed sketches, and color patterns.
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>URL:</b>
			<a href="http://www.hermitagemuseum.org/fcgi-bin/db2www/qbicSearch.mac/qbic?selLang=English">http://www.hermitagemuseum.org/fcgi-bin/db2www/qbicSearch.mac/qbic?selLang=English
			</a>
			</p>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
